docs.snippet: The improved situation in the war at sea was reflected yesterday in the announcement of further reductions on cargo war-risk rates by commercial marine insurance underwriters. At the same time evidence that the War Shipping Administration expects the...
docs.lead_paragraph: The improved situation in the war at sea was reflected yesterday in the announcement of further reductions on cargo war-risk rates by commercial marine insurance underwriters. At the same time evidence that the War Shipping Administration expects the present comparatively favorable situation to continue improving was seen in the disclosure by officials of that agency that it will no longer issue schedules quoting war-risk rates on export shipments.

docs.lead_paragraph: MONTEVIDEO, Uruguay, Nov. 12 (U.P.) -- United States Ambassador Norman Armour has informally protested to Argentina against the Buenos Aires police treatment of the local representative of the Coordinator of InterAmerican Affairs over a shipment of anti-Nazi posters, reports reaching here said today.
